import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['delay'])]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["delay"].median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Delay Time (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['distance'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='distance', y='distance', data=data, estimator=lambda x: len(x) / len(data) * 100, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():0.2f}")
    ax.set(xlabel='Distance', ylabel='Percentage of Flights')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    data = data.head(10)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="counts", y="origin", hue="destination", data=data, dodge=False)
    ax.set(xlabel='Number of Flights', ylabel='Origin', title='What is the most common origin and destination for flights?')
    ax.legend(loc='lower right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['time'] = data['date'].dt.time
    sns.scatterplot(x='distance', y='delay', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between delay time and distance?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year_month'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')
    flights_by_date = data.groupby('year_month').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='year_month', y='counts', data=flights_by_date)
    ax.set(xlabel='Year-Month', ylabel='Number of Flights')
    ax.axhline(y=flights_by_date['counts'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
